useLayoutEffect:-
useLayoutEffect almost useEffect jaisa hota hai, lekin yeh browser ke screen paint hone se pehle run hota hai.

useEffect → render ke baad
useLayoutEffect → render ke turant baad, but screen dikhne se pehle
Kyu use hota hai?

Jab tumhe DOM ka size, height, width, scroll position wagairah nikalna ho aur flicker na aaye.


useLayoutEffect(() => {
  console.log(divRef.current.offsetHeight);
}, []);


Example:-
import { useRef, useLayoutEffect } from "react";

function Example() {
  const boxRef = useRef();

  useLayoutEffect(() => {
    boxRef.current.style.background = "red";
  }, []);

  return <div ref={boxRef}>Hello</div>;
}


Difference

useEffect(() => {
  // screen pe pehle dikh jayega
  // fir yeh chalega
});
});



useLayoutEffect(() => {
  // pehle yeh chalega
  // fir screen dikhegi
});


Kab use karna chahiye?
DOM measurement
Scroll set karna
Element ki height/width lena
Flicker avoid karna

Kab nahi?

Normal API call ya data fetch ke liye useEffect hi use karo
